description:
Listeria contaminated fruit details-
If you recently bought fruit from Trader Joe's, Costco, a Wegman's  or Sam's Club, you might want to hold off enjoying it and making sure it's not part of a fruit recall.

The Wawona Packing Company of California is recalling peaches, nectarines, plums and pluots that maybe potentially contaminated with Listeria monocytognes. They were sold at the two wholesale clubs and food market. While no illness has yet been reported, consumers are being urged to not eat the fruit as Listeria can bring on serious illness and even potentially death.

Seniors, pregnant women and children and anyone with a weak immune systems are at the most risk for Listeria. Listeria can cause miscarriages and stillbirths. The infection symptoms include nausea, stiffness, severe headache, diarrhea, high fever and abdominal pain.

The food markets have been contacted, according to Wawona, and the produce is being pulled from the shelves. The recall was trigged by an internal test result. According to the Food and Drug Administration, the factory packing lines have been shuttered and equipment has been replaced.

The FDA says subsequent testing has revealed that any Listeria issue is gone at this point.

The fruit in question was packed between June 1 and July 12.

The FDA has listed photos of the packaged fruit for consumer view. Visit here 
http://www.fda.gov/Safety/Recalls/ucm405945.htm

Wegman's, a Rochester supermarket, is also issuing a recall on the Wawona fruit, telling customers not to eat the "Sweet 2 Eat" organic and regular white and yellow peaches as well as black plums and nectarines. The recall also involves baked goods at Wegman's made with those fruit products and sold between June 1 and this past Sunday.
title: Listeria contaminated fruit details

Es war Chucks spontane Idee, eine unangekündigte Akustiksession von Hot Water Music vor dem ausverkauften FZW in Dortmund zu spielen - exklusiv für die Cardinal Sessions und natürlich für die wartenden Fans von Hot Water Music.

Performed wurden zwei Songs des neuen Albums "Exister", dem ersten seit acht Jahren: "State of Grace" und "The Traps" zu dem in vielen Reviews im positiven Sinne zu lesen war: „Was gibt es da noch groß zu sagen, es sind und bleiben eben Hot Water Music." 

Es brauchte ein paar Sekunden, bis wirklich alle Wartenden verstanden hatten, was gerade passiert und versammelten sich dann schließlich noch während des ersten Songs „State of Grace" um Chris und Chuck, die auch akustisch wie immer alles gaben und sichtlich Spaß bei dieser spontanen Aktion hatten. Das sind die seltenen, intimen Momente, die man als Fan nicht vergisst - festgehalten in zwei Videos:
__________________________________________________

Last week Hot Water Music played a sold out show at the FZW in Dortmund. Chuck thought it would be cool for the band to perform a spontaneous, unannounced acoustic set before the show - exclusively for Cardinal Sessions (and the lucky fans waiting outside).

They played two songs from the new album "Exister", their first in eight years. Critics agree that both songs, "State of Grace" and "The Traps", embody Hot Water Music at its best: "What more is there to say? They are and remain Hot Water Music."

It took a few moments before the people waiting outside realized just what was happening. But as you can see at the end of "State of Grace", it didn't take long for people to realize just how lucky they were to witness such a rare, intimate moment - captured for you in two videos.

This clip was taken at Antwerp zoo, in Belgium.  There are a pair of birds in this aviary, and they were one of four species in the zoo, and three in this particular row of aviaries.  Other curassows kept at Antwerp are Red billed curassows, helmeted curassow, and great curassow.  There also used to be Wattled curassow, but these are no longer registered with ISIS, so I am not entirely sure what has happened to them.

This species is one of two species of whistling curassows.  The other being the wattled curassow.  This species is one of four crax curassows with yellow facial skin, but this one has the characteristic yellow knob on it's bill.  It is found in Northern Venezuela, and some small areas of Columbia.

description:
So you found yourself a possible vacant property and are now looking for the owner to get more information. If you're just starting off, this is a good problem to have. It means that you're out there, you're doing something and you're coming across houses that either have a lot of snow that hasn't been shoveled or, now that it's spring time, you're going to be seeing houses with grass that's knee high. Let's look at some of the avenues you can take to find the owner of a vacant property.

1. Check the owner's mailing address on the tax records.

Now there's two slots for the address: one slot is for the actual property and the second for the mailing address. If that mailing address is different from where the property is located, then you've just figured out where that owner lives.

2. Leave a note or reverse bandit sign.

If the owner lives nearby and he checks up on the property once a month, or once a quarter, even if he's out of state — if you leave a note there, he's bound to get it, take a look at it and hopefully he'll reach out to you that way.

You can also leave a reverse bandit sign. This is a tactic that I use where on my bandit signs (where it says "we buy houses"), I flip it around and use a sharpie to write "Interested in buying your house. Call me." The phone number is already on the other side so if he's interested, he'll definitely see a yard sign in his lawn and he'll reach out to you.

3. Send a letter to the property. It may forward to the owner.

Remember, in #1 we were sending it to the mailing address, but what if the mailing address and the property address are the same? The reason you want to do this is because the post office gives you about a year worth of time to forward letters over. So if that forwarding is still in place within that year, that letter—even though you sent it to the property—will forward over to where the owner is living.

4. Talk to the neighbors.

Be active and be proactive. Go around and knock on doors and talk to the neighbors. I would talk to the guy on the left, right, behind and front — whatever it takes until people start telling you "I've never talked to that guy!" 

This worked very well for the house that my parents live. I actually had my dad go over and talk to the neighbors. All he did was say, "Hey listen, we know this house is vacant, it's an eye-soar for the neighborhood, and all we want to do is try to buy it or have a family that's going to move into it." And then my dad gave my business card to that neighbor and she said, "You know what, listen, I know this neighbor pretty well. She left me her new address and her phone number. I'll give her a call and explain to her what you said. And if she's interested, she'll call you." And sure enough, just by that action, that 5 minutes my dad took to talk to the neighbor, I was able to get a phone call and we secured that deal for 50% of market value.

5. Hire a skip tracer.

If you're still working a 9-5 job and don't have time to do any of the above, hire a skip tracer and they'll take care of it. I've seen skip tracers that are able to provide email addresses, Facebook accounts, phone numbers. and at the very least, where that owner is living. 

There you have it! Now get out there and look for more vacant properties! You may come up with some of your own suggestions other than the ones mentioned here so please feel free to share them with us in the comments below.
title: 5 Ways to Find the Owner of a Vacant Property (Absentee Owners) - Thinkademy

description:
Washing, cleaning, and sterilizing bottles is one of the real chores in raising a newborn. At times it seems like we spend more time at the sink than we do actually holding our baby. The Philips AVENT Sterilizer can make this chore a bit easier. While there are certainly things that I like about this sterilizer there are other attributes that really limit how often (and long) we can use this product 

**** This sterilizer will warp sippy cups***** 
***** We have difficulty/ it is impossible to use with large bottles***** 

The first attribute is not the fault of Philips, since the sterilizer produces steam in semi-pressurize environment it accidently melts/warps some plastic items. I mentioned sippy cups, but it also melted a new coffee thermos that I wanted sterilized. 

The second point doesn't make much sense, but Dr. Brown's BPA Free Polypropylene Bottle, 3 Pack, 8 oz are too big to be used in this sterilizer. This is a bit of a head-scratcher as to why they made a device that is about 1/2" too short to accommodate a very common type of bottle. 

A few other notes 

- Very, very easy to use and set-up. Grandma will have no problem learning how to use this sterilizer 
- Takes up a lot of counter space - more than a standard coffee maker. 
- Be careful with placement, the exiting steam may ruin your wood cabinets 
- The directions are poor, and while it is easy to set-up it would be nice if the directions demonstrated how everything fits together. 

Final verdict - This is a great product for parents with children less than 6 months, however it quickly becomes obsolete as your child moves into bigger bottles and sippy cups.

I received this item for reviewing purposes
title: Philips AVENT Electric Steam Sterilizer - Perfect for sterilizing AVENT baby bottles

description:
Get the beard wax here: http://oxhorn.it/best-beard-wax

Read my guide to using beard wax, and see more beard wax brands: http://www.growabeardnow.com/beard-wax/

How to Use Beard Wax

1) After you dry your beard, open your tin of beard wax and scrape off a good thumbnail-sized dab of beard wax with your thumb.

2) Rub the wax into the palm of your hand until it melts. This is important! If you do not melt the wax, then you'll leave clumps of it in your beard that will stick with you all day. Thankfully, beard wax is much easier to melt than mustache wax, so you should have no problem. Once the wax is melted, rub your hands together.

3) Apply it to your beard by swiping your hands in a downwards motion on the front of your beard. Do this over and over again until you get the beard wax all over the front of your beard. If your beard is long and thick, you may need to get another chunk and add it to your beard.

4) Grab a beard comb and gently comb your beard to shape. You'll notice that your beard will stay in whichever direction you comb it!
title: Beard Wax - How to Apply Beard Wax

En embriología, Saco Vitelino se refiere a un anexo embrionario, que produce y transporta nutrientes y oxígeno hacia el embrión; y de éste, elimina desechos metabólicos como CO2. Su nombre se debe a que posee forma de saco.
Se ha descubierto que el saco vitelino desempeña funciones importantísimas en el desarrollo embrionario. Además, se sabe que este anexo es la primera fuente sanguínea del embrión, con lo cuál se transforma en un constituyente vital para el embrión, sin el cuál no sobreviviría.
El saco vitelino está cubierto por una delgada capa mucosa y una pared más interna rica en vasos sanguíneos que serán aportados al comunicado embrionario.
Luego de la gastrulación, el saco vitelino queda suspendido y sostenido del cuerpo embrionario, con lo que da forma al conducto vitelino.
Mediante el desarrollo fetal, y principalmente a partir de la 9 y 10 semana de desarrollo, el saco vitelino comienza a degenerar de manera natural por diversas causas, como su compresión debido al aumento del espacio ocupado por el amnios. Durante el periodo temprano del desarrollo embrionario, el saco vitelino es la estructura de mayor dimensión, con una forma ovalada, pero que con el desarrollo, adquiere una apariencia periforme.
No se conoce cuánto tiempo permanece activo el saco vitelino.

It is the first element seen in the gestational sac during pregnancy, usually at 5 weeks gestation. It is a critical landmark, identifying a true gestation sac. It is reliably seen early in human pregnancy using ultrasound.
The yolk-sac is situated on the ventral aspect of the embryo; it is lined by extra-embyronic endoderm, outside of which is a layer of extra-embryonic mesenchyme, derived from the mesoderm.
Blood is conveyed to the wall of the sac by the primitive aorta, and after circulating through a wide-meshed capillary plexus, is returned by the vitelline veins to the tubular heart of the embryo. This constitutes the vitelline circulation, and by means of it nutritive material is absorbed from the yolk-sac and conveyed to the embryo.
At the end of the fourth week the yolk-sac presents the appearance of a small pear-shaped vesicle (umbilical vesicle) opening into the digestive tube by a long narrow tube, the vitelline duct.
The vesicle can be seen in the after-birth as a small, somewhat oval-shaped body whose diameter varies from 1 mm. to 5 mm.; it is situated between the amnion and the chorion and may lie on or at a varying distance from the placenta.
As a rule the duct undergoes complete obliteration during the seventh week, but in about two percent of cases its proximal part persists as a diverticulum from the small intestine, Meckel's diverticulum, which is situated about 60cm proximal to the ileocecal valve, and may be attached by a fibrous cord to the abdominal wall at the umbilicus.
Sometimes a narrowing of the lumen of the ileum is seen opposite the site of attachment of the duct.
title: The yolk sac o saco vitelino en un embarazo de 6 semanas de edad Gestacional.

description:
Rollade

Stukjes vlees samen oprollen, vastbinden en geduldig braden... De rollade is van oorsprong een mooie manier om geen vlees te verspillen. Maar inmiddels is het een feestmaal op zich, waar hele mooie stukken vlees in worden verwerkt in tal van (kruiden) variaties. 

Grenzeloze rollades
Vlees oprollen en met touw vastbinden gebeurt zeker niet alleen in Nederland. In Duitsland eet men bijvoorbeeld Rollbraten (altijd varken), in Engeland de rolled roast (vaak juist rundvlees), in frankrijk de Roti de porc, al dan niet gebraden in melk, en in Italië de carne arrotolata. Zeker in de laatste variant gaat het vlees vaak vergezelfd van rijke vulling. Groenten, kruiden, champignons, maar ook kaas of fruit: een creatieve kok of slager weet wel raad met rollade.

Welk vlees?
De moderne Nederlandse rollade bestaat uit grotere stukken van de rug of de buik waar alle beenderen, overtollig vet en zenuwen uit vewijderd zijn. Een rollade kan van alle vleessoorten worden gemaakt: rund, kalf, lam, kip of kalkoen. Of van combinaties met bijvoorbeeld rosbief, waarbij het vlees dat het snelst gaart aan de binnenkant van de rollade zit.
title: Rollade van keurslager de Haas

description:
The African Center for Economic Transformation (ACET)  is the local managing partner for theThe African Center for Economic Transformation (ACET)  is the local managing partner for the Rockefeller Foundation's Informal City Dialogues, Accra (ICD Accra). It is our task to conduct these dialogues in the city and to bring together a diverse group of citizens representing public, private, civic, industry, non-profits, local philanthropies, workers, street vendors, urban poor groups, academe, women and youth who will consider scenarios for the future of Accra in 2040.

Community focal persons have been enrolled to help us reach people from three excluded communities;Ga Mashie and Fadama (also known as Sodom and Gomorrah - the largest slum settlement in Accra), and Nima which is a predominantly muslim community also referred to as "zongos", whose inhabitants are often migrants from the regions, working in informal sectors and traditionally seen as an excluded minority.

An important legacy that we want to leave in excluded communities from this project, is the opportunity for people to imagine a better future for themselves and for their city. In order to share the ideas of this process more effectively, we are launching a short YouTube video competition called Accra Future-Now Video Competition.

78 volunteers took part in 3-minute video recording, to answer three short questions on film:
a. What are your hopes and fears for the future of your community?
b. What would you like to change about where you live?
c. How will things improve when that change comes?

The project team will select 10 finalists whose videos will be compiled into a short DVD, these recordings will be placed on the ICD ACCRA YouTube website for broadcast during April.

The top three winners will cash prizes and support to encourage them in community advocacy. Names will be announced in April and winners invited to attend a presentation dinner on Tuesday April 23rd 2013 in Accra.

description: Ibn al-Nafis wrote the Theologus Autodidactus as a defense of "the system of Islam and the Muslims' doctrines on the missions of Prophets, the religious laws, the resurrection of the body, and the transitoriness of the world." The book presents rational arguments for bodily resurrection and the immortality of the human soul, using both demonstrative reasoning and material from the hadith corpus as forms of evidence. Later Islamic scholars viewed this work as a response to Avicenna's metaphysical argument on spiritual resurrection (as opposed to bodily resurrection), which was earlier criticized by al-Ghazali.
title: Resurrection In Islamic Philosophy.

♥My Outfit Planning & Clothing Care Tips:
1) Plan Ahead- 
Choose outfit options ahead of time, set them out & try them on. 
Use a foldable garment rack ( http://bit.ly/1vkYnNK ) to clearly view your options. 

2)Think Like A Stylist-
Choose the entire ensemble ahead of time, from accessories, to the makeup. You can even plan your hair style. Use http://www.Polyvore.com to help create outfit collage ideas. Save them on your computer, and keep them in a dated folder, or pin them onto Pinterest for future outfit ideas. 

3) Mix & Match Price Points-
Express your style within your budget. Shop eBay for new or pre-owned items. Thrift stores, and poshmark have some great options too. Mix your classic (more expensive) pieces, with treasures you find at a lower cost.

4) Use A Tailor-
I use a tailor for some of my jeans, skirts, special occasion dresses, or anything that doesn't fit quite right. A proper fit is key to looking and feeling your best in your clothing. 

5) Take Good Care-
Read the labels, and follow the instructions on how to clean your clothing. Use detergents that are gentle, and do not strip clothing of it's color or texture. Follow the guidelines for drying and ironing also. Try using a steamer ( http://bit.ly/1svJq93) instead of an iron.

Everybody is familiar with the term 'trading'. Most of us have traded in our everyday life, although we may not even know that we have done so. Essentially, everything you buy in a store is trading money for the goods you want.

At tradimo you will learn how to trade the financial markets online — but what exactly is trading online? This video will introduce you to the exiting world of online trading - be it forex, stocks or commodities. 

Prices are determined by supply and demand - in our everyday world and in online trading. 
When more people want to buy something, the price usually goes up. So when you buy shares and the company posts great results and more people want to buy the stock, you can sell the shares at a higher price and make money.

The world of trading was originally limited to large institutions and funds. The internet has made online trading possible for everyone. This market is now open to you. You can also learn to trade. And this is where tradimo helps you.
